svg.text: Read the conversation between two new students. Are the statements that follow
你好！我叫明明。我是学生。
我也是学生。你的老师是谁？
白老师也是我的老师！我们是同学。
The first new student’s name is Mingming.
The first student says that he likes his teacher.
These students learn that they are classmates.
For thousands of years, ink seals were used as official signatures. People still
make traditional name seals today, but they are often used for personal enjoyment or as an
artistic signature. Can you tell to whom these seals belong? (Hint: Remember that in the past
Chinese was not written from left to right.)
